Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and halve 
@sweet potatoes{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Cut 
@broccoli florets{8%ounces} into bitesize pieces if necessary. Quarter @lime{1}.

> For speedier spud prep, skip the peeling!

== Scallion Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add 
scallion whites; cook until slightly softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, 
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Vegetables ==

While rice cooks, toss sweet potato on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a 
drizzle of oil, salt, and @pepper{}.

Toss broccoli on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If broccoli finishes before sweet potato, remove from sheet and continue 
> roasting sweet potato.

== Honey Miso Dressing ==

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @miso sauce concentrate{1}, 
@honey{2%teaspoons}, and a big squeeze of lime juice to taste.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoons} with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} 
to taste. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling 
consistency.

== Fried Eggs ==

When veggies are almost done, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably 
nonstick, over medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry to 
preference. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a fork and season with salt and pepper.

Add broccoli to bowl with honey miso dressing; toss to coat.

Divide rice between bowls; top with broccoli and drizzle with remaining dressing 
in bowl. Add sweet potato and fried eggs. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo and sprinkle 
with scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.